ants-terminal (0.7.49-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Three follow-up fixes to user reports against 0.7.48 — the
    About menu's OK buttons silently no-op'd again, the GitHub
    Public/Private badge wanted to live next to the git branch on
    the left, and the Background Tasks chip showed phantom counts
    of tasks that had long since exited.
  * Fixed: both Help → About dialogs now dismiss on the OK button.
    The 0.7.35 attempt only swapped the dialog type (QMessageBox →
    QDialog); both still went through exec(). On KDE/KWin +
    Qt 6.11 with the frameless + WA_TranslucentBackground
    MainWindow, the nested QEventLoop exec() opens does not
    surface the dialog as the active input window — the OK button
    never receives focus and the click silently no-ops. Both
    handlers now use the heap + WA_DeleteOnClose + show() +
    raise() + activateWindow() pattern that already works for
    other dialogs in this stack. About Qt dropped
    QMessageBox::aboutQt for a custom QDialog with the same
    treatment.
  * Fixed: Background Tasks chip now reflects only tasks that are
    genuinely running. parseTranscript performs a liveness sweep
    at the end — unfinished tasks whose output file is gone or
    whose mtime is older than 60 s are flipped to finished. The
    2 s status timer drives refreshBgTasksButton so the sweep
    keeps firing while the transcript itself is silent.
  * Changed: GitHub Public/Private badge moved to the left side
    of the status bar, next to the git-branch chip (was on the
    right via addPermanentWidget, shipped 0.7.45). Restyled to
    match the branch chip's rounded bgSecondary fill + border
    frame while keeping the green-public / red-private foreground
    colour.

