ants-terminal (0.7.40-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Performance. Two Tier 3 perf items from ROADMAP.md § 0.7.x ⚡ / 🏗
    Tier 3 — structural retired in one bundle: scroll-region rotate plus
    a zero-copy VtBatch hop across the worker→GUI thread boundary. Both
    are observably equivalent at the API level — existing
    tests/features/scroll_region_rotate/ and
    tests/features/threaded_parse_equivalence/ regressions pass
    unchanged — so the win is throughput / cost, not visible behaviour.
  * Changed: TerminalGrid::scrollUp / scrollDown use std::rotate.
    Replaced the per-iteration m_screenLines.erase + insert loop with a
    single rotate over [scrollTop, scrollBottom], gated by a
    pool-salvage / scrollback-push pre-pass and a fresh-blank
    post-pass. The CSI 2J doubling-guard window check runs once per
    batch instead of per iteration. m_scrollback cap enforcement
    collapses from N pop_front passes to one. On CSI 100 S against an
    80-row screen, row-shift cost drops from O(count × rows) memmoves
    (8000) to O(rows) (80).
  * Changed: VtStream::batchReady carries VtBatchPtr instead of
    const VtBatch &. New alias
    using VtBatchPtr = std::shared_ptr<const VtBatch>; in vtstream.h.
    Qt's queued-connection plumbing must own dispatched parameters, so
    the prior const T & signal forced a deep copy of the actions vector
    + rawBytes QByteArray on every worker→GUI hop. The shared_ptr wrap
    reduces the cross-thread payload to a 16-byte atomic refcount bump;
    the underlying VtBatch lives on the heap and is not duplicated.
    Both emit sites (flushBatch, onPtyFinished) build via
    std::make_shared<VtBatch>(); TerminalWidget::onVtBatch signature is
    now void onVtBatch(VtBatchPtr batch) with field access via batch->…
  * Locked by tests/features/vtbatch_zero_copy/ (5 source-grep
    invariants pinning the cross-thread signal shape). Behavioural
    equivalence stays covered by
    tests/features/threaded_parse_equivalence/; rotation correctness
    stays covered by the 8 algorithm-agnostic invariants in
    tests/features/scroll_region_rotate/.

