ants-terminal (0.7.38-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Feature. Background-tasks status-bar surface for Claude Code.
    User request 2026-04-25: "a button on the status bar when there
    are background tasks being run. We then click the button to view
    what Claude Code shows for the background tasks. The button opens
    a dialog showing the live update info on the background tasks."
    Claude Code can spawn long-running tasks via Bash or Task with
    run_in_background:true. The TUI shows a sidebar listing them with
    their tail output; users dropping into a different tab to keep
    working had no way to see those tasks from Ants Terminal.
  * Added: Background-tasks tracker (claudebgtasks.{h,cpp}). A pure
    parser walks the active session's transcript JSONL, recognizing
    tool_use blocks whose input.run_in_background == true (start) and
    tool_result blocks whose toolUseResult.backgroundTaskId is set
    (confirmation, with the on-disk output path extracted from the
    result body). Completion / kill state is derived from subsequent
    BashOutput results carrying status: "completed" | "killed" |
    "failed" and from KillShell tool calls. Static parseTranscript()
    is testable without a watcher.
  * Added: Status-bar button (mainwindow.{h,cpp}). Sibling to Review
    Changes; same fixed sizePolicy contract. Hidden by default; shown
    only while runningCount() > 0 for the active tab's session. Label
    is "Background Tasks (N)"; tooltip discloses running + total.
    Re-targeted on tab switch via refreshStatusBarForActiveTab.
  * Added: Live-tail dialog (claudebgtasksdialog.{h,cpp}). Mirrors the
    0.7.37 Review Changes live-update model. QFileSystemWatcher covers
    each task's .output file plus the transcript path; 200 ms debounce
    timer collapses bursts of fileChanged signals into one render.
    Skip-identical-HTML guard plus capture-vbar-before-setHtml +
    restore-after with qMin(..., maximum()) clamp preserves scroll on
    real content changes. "Was at bottom" detection pins users to the
    bottom across appends when they are tailing.
  * Locked by a new tests/features/claude_bg_tasks_button/ spec + test
    (10 invariants — source-grep harness, no Qt link).

