    live refreshes. Two-layer guard around setHtml inside the
    showDiffViewer finalize lambda. (1) An lastHtml shared_ptr<QString>
    cache threaded through runProbes and finalize lets finalize
    early-return when the new render is byte-identical to the
    previous one — the common case during idle tics. Selection,
    cursor, and scroll are byte-perfectly preserved. (2) When
    content does change, vertical/horizontal scroll-bar values are
    captured before setHtml and restored after, clamped to
    bar->maximum() so a shorter render after a commit doesn't over-
    scroll. First-render carve-out keeps the initial paint at the top.
  * Locked by a new tests/features/review_changes_scroll_preserve/
    spec + test (6 invariants — source-grep harness scoped to the
    showDiffViewer body).

