ants-terminal (0.7.28-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Audit pipeline I — process-side robustness. Three ROADMAP §
    0.7.12 Tier 2 items shipped together as bundle 0.7.28:
    per-tool timeout overrides, incremental QProcess output drain
    with a 64 MiB cap, and a distinct tool-crash warning that no
    longer hides as "0 findings."
  * Changed: AuditCheck::timeoutMs — per-check QProcess timeout.
    Was: m_timeout->start(30000) hard-coded for every check. Slow
    tools (cppcheck on a 500k-line tree, semgrep, osv-scanner,
    trufflehog, clang-tidy, clazy) routinely exceeded the 30 s
    cap. Now: int timeoutMs = 30000 trailing field on AuditCheck,
    m_timeout->start(check.timeoutMs) at the use site, and a
    calibration loop at the end of populateChecks bumps known-slow
    tools to 60 s / 90 s / 120 s. Locked by
    tests/features/audit_per_tool_timeout (4 invariants).
  * Changed: incremental QProcess output drain with 64 MiB cap.
    Was: readAllStandardOutput() called once inside
    onCheckFinished. QProcess buffered without bound — a runaway
    semgrep could buffer hundreds of MB before the timeout fired.
    Now: ctor wires readyReadStandardOutput /
    readyReadStandardError to new drain slots that append to
    m_currentOutput / m_currentError incrementally; on overflow
    the process is killed and m_outputOverflowed flagged.
    onCheckFinished reads from the buffers instead of the live
    process. New connectProcessSignals helper centralises the
    three connections. Locked by
    tests/features/audit_incremental_output_drain (6 invariants).
