    chunks, plus a menubar-opacity fix reported mid-session.
  * Security: OSC 8 URI cap (MAX_OSC8_URI_BYTES = 2 KiB) and Kitty
    APC chunk-buffer cap (MAX_KITTY_CHUNK_BYTES = 32 MiB) in
    src/terminalgrid.h. Previously both accumulators were bounded
    only by the VT parser's per-envelope 10 MB ceiling, so hostile
    output could wedge tens of GB into per-row HyperlinkSpan copies
    or into the APC staging buffer before any downstream guard ran.
    Oversized OSC 8 URIs take the invalid-scheme drop path so
    following text prints unlinked. The APC chunk path clears +
    shrink_to_fits the staging buffer on cap breach so a subsequent
    m=0 close sees an empty buffer rather than attacker-prepended
    garbage. Regression test tests/features/osc8_apc_memory_caps
    locks 5 invariants — pre-fix source fails INV-OSC8-B and
    INV-APC-B, post-fix all 5 pass.
  * Fixed: menubar renders opaque under WA_TranslucentBackground
    (MainWindow::applyTheme). User report 2026-04-24: "the
    background of the menubar is transparent." The top-level QSS
    cascade could race with the compositor damage rect, letting
    whatever sat behind the window bleed through before polish.
    applyTheme now installs a belt-and-suspenders opaque fill on
    m_menuBar — QPalette::Window = theme.bgSecondary so
    autoFillBackground lays down an opaque fill before QSS paints,
    plus a widget-local setStyleSheet(QMenuBar ...) block so the
    menubar's own style engine polishes independently. Mirrors the
    pattern already used on the custom title bar and status bar.

