ants-terminal (0.7.14-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Three Claude Code integration robustness fixes from the 0.7.12+1
    re-review checkpoint. All three failed silently — no errors, no
    degraded-mode logs — so symptoms were a transcript-driven UI
    state that stopped updating, or a project appearing under the
    wrong name in the picker. All three now have targeted
    fixture-based regression tests.
  * Fixed: Claude transcript tail window drops events larger than
    32 KB. parseTranscriptForState read the final 32 KB of the JSONL
    transcript and skipped the first line after the seek as
    likely-truncated; when the final event was a user tool_result
    carrying inline file contents, the window landed inside that
    one event and the parser returned zero events, freezing state.
    Replaced with a doubling-grow window (32 KB → 4 MiB cap) that
    only trims a potentially-partial prefix line when the buffer
    contains at least two newlines.
  * Fixed: Claude transcript dialog silently drops thinking content
    blocks. ClaudeTranscriptDialog::formatEntry only rendered text,
    tool_use, and tool_result; thinking fell into an implicit else
    that discarded the block. Now rendered as italicized, dimmed
    "Thinking:" paragraphs, distinguishing chain-of-thought from
    the visible reply.
  * Fixed: decodeProjectPath mangles project names with embedded
    hyphens. Claude Code encodes absolute paths by replacing every
    "/" with "-" — lossy, since leaf-hyphens and segment-separators
    encode identically. Rewrote as a greedy left-to-right
    filesystem-probing walker: at each hyphen, prefer the "/" form
    if that directory exists, fall back to "-" (folded into the
    segment name) otherwise. extractCwdFromTranscript remains the
    preferred source of truth; the probe-based decoder is the
    last-resort fallback.
  * Tests: new tests/features/claude_transcript_robustness lane —
    six-invariant regression test (tail-window growth past 40 KB
    trailing events, 4 MiB growth cap, leaf-name hyphen
    preservation, intermediate-segment hyphen preservation,
    missing-filesystem-hint fallback to legacy behavior, canonical
    repo-style decoding). Verified to fail against pre-fix code on
    the regression invariants.
  * Changed: no API or config changes. Pure bugfix release.

