ants-terminal (0.7.5-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Same-day follow-up to 0.7.4 that resolves the dropdown-menu
    flicker the 0.7.4 Known Issue section called out. Root cause
    finally pinpointed via the Debug Mode instrumentation that
    shipped in 0.7.4: Fusion's QWidgetAnimator was creating a 60 Hz
    QPropertyAnimation(target=QWidget, prop=geometry) cycle on the
    idle window, each completion driving a full LayoutRequest →
    UpdateRequest → Paint cascade. Neither setEffectEnabled(
    UI_AnimateMenu, false) nor QMainWindow::setAnimated(false)
    covers the style-hint-driven cycle — only the
    QStyle::SH_Widget_Animation_Duration hint does.
  * Fixed: dropdown-menu flicker (root cause). NoAnimStyle
    QProxyStyle in src/main.cpp zeroes SH_Widget_Animation_Duration
    and SH_Widget_Animate, wrapped around Fusion at startup. Idle-
    log result: 0 QPropertyAnimation events (was ≈62 Hz in 0.7.4).
    Total event volume dropped >99% (29 096 → 62 log lines in 4 s
    idle). Pinned by the new no_anim_style feature test.
  * Fixed: Debug Mode animation-creation hook — switched from
    QEvent::ChildAdded (child vtable not ready) to ChildPolished
    (fires post-construction), so QPropertyAnimation creation sites
    now log correctly.

