ants-terminal (0.7.4-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * A session's worth of user-facing UI fixes plus a new Debug Mode
    that made them possible. The instrument pinpointed a ~54 Hz
    full-window repaint cascade that had been driving the menubar /
    dropdown / paste-dialog flicker across several releases.
  * Added: Debug Mode (src/debuglog.{h,cpp}). 14 independent
    category toggles (Paint, Events, Input, PTY, VT, Render,
    Plugins, Network, Config, Audit, Claude, Signals, Shell,
    Session) via ANTS_DEBUG env var or Tools → Debug Mode menu.
    Log at ~/.local/share/ants-terminal/debug.log.
  * Added: OSC 133 prompt-on-new-line guard — terminal-side
    equivalent of zsh's PROMPT_SP, works for any shell that emits
    OSC 133 A at prompt start.
