ants-terminal (0.7.1-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * First of the 0.8.0 multiplexing roadmap items lands ahead of the
    larger mux-server / remote-control work: SSH ControlMaster auto-
    multiplexing from the bookmark dialog. A second tab to the same
    host now reuses the first tab's session, skipping the full auth
    handshake — same precedent as kitty's ssh kitten, Warp's SSH
    blocks, and iTerm2's SSH profiles.
  * Added: SSH ControlMaster auto-multiplexing. Connects opened from
    the SSH Manager carry -o ControlMaster=auto, -o ControlPath=
    $HOME/.ssh/cm-%r@%h:%p, and -o ControlPersist=10m when the new
    ssh_control_master config key is true (default). Opt-out via
    ~/.config/ants-terminal/config.json for sites that forbid
    lingering multiplex sockets by policy. $HOME resolves in-process
    via QDir::homePath() so the ControlPath works under dash / POSIX
    sh; %r@%h:%p are OpenSSH ControlPath substitution tokens and
    survive shell quoting intact. The three -o options precede the
    [user@]host destination for parity with OpenSSH documentation.
  * Tests: new ssh_control_master feature test pins six invariants
    — default + explicit-false produce zero Control* tokens,
    explicit-true emits all three, $HOME resolution replaces any
    literal tilde, %r@%h:%p survives shell quoting, the flags
    precede the destination arg, and they coexist with legacy -p /
    -i / extraArgs without interference.

