    in-app QShortcut fallback stays active on GNOME Shell.
  * Security: plugin capability audit UI renders every declared
    permission as a revocable checkbox under Settings → Plugins,
    persisted to config.plugin_grants[<name>] and applied on next
    plugin reload. Image-bomb defenses cap total decoded image bytes
    at 256 MB per terminal across Sixel / Kitty / iTerm2 OSC 1337;
    per-image MAX_IMAGE_DIM = 4096 dimension cap remains in place.
