ants-terminal (0.6.45-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Deferred VT-standards items from the 10th-audit research report
    plus atomic-write hardening for long-lived audit state. The 11th
    periodic audit returned 0 of ~103 actionable findings — baseline
    remains clean.
  * OSC 10 / 11 / 12 colour queries. Apps (delta, neovim, bat, lazygit,
    fzf, jj, most termenv-based Go TUIs) probe the terminal for
    default fg / bg / cursor colour with \e]10;?\e\\ etc. to auto-
    detect dark vs light themes without relying on the unreliable
    COLORFGBG env var. Response is the xterm 16-bit-per-channel form
    \e]<n>;rgb:RRRR/GGGG/BBBB\e\\. Only the query form is honoured —
    the set form is deliberately silently dropped so default fg/bg
    stays theme-driven and in-terminal programs can't inject a theme.
  * DECRQSS (Request Status String). DCS $q requests for DECSTBM
    (scroll-region, r), SGR (current attributes, m), and DECSCUSR
    (cursor shape,  q) now reply with DCS 1 $ r … per the xterm spec.
    Unknown settings reply "invalid" (DCS 0 $ r …) rather than
    dropping silently so callers fall back to defaults. The DECRQSS
    branch gates on the $q prefix before Sixel's q search so Sixel
    image DCS payloads still route to the image handler.
  * Atomic JSON writes via QSaveFile for four long-lived files —
    audit_rule_quality.json (per-fire / per-suppression history,
    written frequently; corruption loses every rule score),
    .audit_cache/trend.json (cumulative per-run severity totals),
    .audit_cache/baseline.json (fingerprints anchoring the "new
    findings only" filter), and the .audit_suppress v1 → v2 migration
    rewrite. Torn writes from crash / kill -9 can no longer corrupt
    any of these. The one-line .audit_suppress append path stays
    non-atomic on purpose — the loader already skips malformed lines.
    config.json and session snapshots already had a tighter fsync-
    then-rename pattern; those were left in place.
  * New feature tests: osc_color_query locks the OSC 10/11/12
    response shape plus the query-only gate (set form MUST NOT
    produce a response, preventing theme injection); decrqss locks
    the DECSTBM / SGR / DECSCUSR replies, the invalid-reply bytes,
    and a Sixel-routing regression guard so the new DECRQSS branch
    can't eat image traffic.

