ants-terminal (0.6.43-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Fix menubar hover flash. The 0.6.42 focus-redirect guards
    narrowed firing but didn't address the root cause — the
    stylesheet defined QMenuBar::item:selected without a matching
    base QMenuBar::item rule, so Qt fell back to the native style
    for the non-selected state and composited native drawing under
    the :selected overlay. Added an explicit transparent-background
    QMenuBar::item base rule plus a :pressed rule so every menubar
    item state is owned entirely by the stylesheet; the 0.6.42
    focus guards remain as defense-in-depth.
  * Session persistence now default-on. Config::sessionPersistence()
    defaulted to false, so users who never toggled Settings →
    General → "Save and restore sessions" lost their tab set on
    every quit. Flipped the default to true to match iTerm2 /
    Kitty / WezTerm / Konsole; users with session_persistence:
    false explicit in config.json still get their opt-out honoured
    (only the absent-key path reads the fallback). The 5-second
    uptime floor in saveAllSessions() still protects against
    crash-on-launch wiping real state.
  * New feature test tests/features/session_persistence_default
    (CTest labels features;fast) pins the three-row truth table:
    missing key → true, explicit true → true, explicit false →
    false. Linked against src/config.cpp only (no GUI dependency).
    Brings feature-test count to 25, total ctest count to 26.
  * Cleaned up a -Wshadow warning at mainwindow.cpp:3921 (the
    Review-Changes finalizer lambda's `const Theme &th` shadowed
    the outer `th`; renamed the lambda-local to `lth`) and dropped
    an unused <cstdlib> include from the new test.

