ants-terminal (0.6.42-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Focus-redirect guard rails. The 0.6.26 auto-return-to-terminal
    handler was firing through two narrow windows where it
    shouldn't — hovering across the File / Edit / View menubar
    produced a visibly flashing highlight, and the paste-
    confirmation dialog's "Paste" button silently swallowed mouse
    clicks (only the &Paste keyboard shortcut worked). Both traced
    back to the same QApplication::focusChanged handler in
    src/mainwindow.cpp.
  * Fix menubar hover flash. The focus-redirect lambda now early-
    returns when QApplication::activePopupWidget() is non-null
    (covers QMenu / QComboBox dropdown / tooltip) and when the
    widget under QCursor::pos() has a QMenu / QMenuBar ancestor
    (covers the menubar itself, which is NOT a popup). Both guards
    are mirrored at the deferred QTimer::singleShot(0, ...) fire
    time so a menu that opens between queue and fire is still
    honored.
  * Fix paste-confirmation dialog click swallow. The redirect now
    walks QApplication::topLevelWidgets() at queue time and early-
    returns on any visible QDialog. Closes the QMessageBox::exec()
    modality-handshake window during which activeModalWidget() can
    briefly return null — which was the exact tick a focusChanged
    event could fire mid-click and rip focus off the button,
    cancelling clicked().
  * New feature test tests/features/focus_redirect_menu_guard
    (CTest labels features;fast) pins six invariants on the
    focusChanged lambda: popup + menu-hover guards at queue and
    fire time, the visible-dialog walk at queue time, and the five
    existing guards (activeModalWidget, QAbstractButton,
    mouseButtons, QDialog parent-chain, CommandPalette) that must
    not regress.

