ants-terminal (0.6.40-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * OSC 133 shell-integration polish. Adds two keyboard-driven
    "last completed command" actions — the iTerm2 CopyLastOutput /
    WezTerm convention — that complement the existing block-at-
    cursor right-click menu with no-selection-needed top-level
    equivalents, surfaced through the View menu, the command
    palette, and configurable keybindings.
  * New TerminalWidget::copyLastCommandOutput() slot walks
    promptRegions() backwards for the most recent region with
    commandEndMs > 0 && hasOutput, then copies the full output via
    outputTextAt(idx). Unlike lastCommandOutput() it is unbounded
    (no 100-line cap) — a user-initiated copy expects the full
    output, not a silently truncated string. The backwards walk
    skips in-progress tails so Ctrl+Alt+O during `sleep 30` copies
    the previous command, never the partial in-progress one.
  * New TerminalWidget::rerunLastCommand() slot uses the same
    backwards-walk / skip-in-progress rule, then writes the command
    text plus \r to the PTY via rerunCommandAt(idx).
  * View-menu entries "Copy Last Command Output" (default
    Ctrl+Alt+O, config key copy_last_output) and "Re-run Last
    Command" (default Ctrl+Alt+R, config key rerun_last_command).
    Both surface automatically in the command palette. The
    Ctrl+Alt+* modifier avoids the taken Ctrl+Shift+O (split pane)
    and Ctrl+Shift+R (record session).
  * Status-bar toasts for discoverability: "Copied N chars of last
    command output" on success, "No completed command to copy
    (enable shell integration)" on failure — a load-bearing hint
    that OSC 133 requires bash/zsh/fish shell-integration hooks.
  * Locked by tests/features/osc133_last_command (CTest labels
    features;fast, part of the release gate).

