ants-terminal (0.6.35-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Hotfix for the 0.6.34 threaded-parse refactor: keystrokes typed
    into the terminal were silently dropped — echo never appeared on
    screen. Twelve PTY-write call sites in TerminalWidget still
    carried pre-0.6.34 `if (m_pty) ptyWrite(...)` guards. Under the
    threaded parse path m_pty is null (the Pty lives on the worker
    thread inside VtStream), so the guard silently swallowed every
    write. Replaced each with either hasPty() (path-agnostic) or an
    unconditional ptyWrite(...) call (the helper is already
    null-safe).
  * shellPid() / shellCwd() / foregroundProcess() now work on the
    worker path via a new ptyChildPid() helper that reads from
    whichever path is active. The PID is written once by forkpty()
    during startShell's blocking-queued invocation so the cross-
    thread read is synchronised and mutex-free.
  * New tests/features/threaded_ptywrite_gating/ regression test.
    Source-grep inspection: no `if (m_pty)` / `&& m_pty)` / `!m_pty`
    gate may appear outside the four allowlisted functions
    (ptyWrite, ptyChildPid, startShell, recalcGridSize,
    ~TerminalWidget). Ground-truth verified.

