ants-terminal (0.6.28-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * End-to-end feature review + status-bar overflow polish. New
    ElidedLabel widget caps the three status-bar text slots (git branch,
    transient message, foreground process) so long strings truncate with
    "…" instead of pushing sibling widgets off-screen. Same treatment
    applied to the window title-bar label, the "Claude: …" label, and
    the audit-dialog status label.
  * Quake-mode toggle no longer auto-hides the window 200 ms after a
    show toggle. The finished→hide() slot from the previous hide toggle
    persisted on the reused QPropertyAnimation; now disconnected before
    every start() and only re-attached on the hide branch.
  * Resize (both main-screen simple-copy and alt-screen paths) now
    preserves the per-line combining-char side table. Pre-0.6.28 every
    resize wiped accents / ZWJ / diacritics because the copy walked
    cells only. New tests/features/combining_on_resize feature test
    pins the behaviour — fails against pre-fix code, passes on fix.
  * Config + session writes now fsync the temp file before atomic
    rename, closing the kernel-crash data-loss window between close()
    and rename() on ext4 data=ordered.
  * Auto-profile rule regex compilation is cached across the 2 s
    poll tick (was recompiled per-rule per-tick), and invalid patterns
    are detected via QRegularExpression::isValid() and warned once
    instead of silently never matching.

